org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication

Class IdentificationResponseMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.Message
      • org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.IdentificationResponseMessage

  • public class IdentificationResponseMessage
extends Message
    This message is sent to the client as a reply to a IdentificationMessage. It contains details about the success of the log in process.
    v1.0 Initial release
    v1.1 added login name (split up of name into display and login name)
    Version:
    v1.1 (Raphael Stoeckli, 23.10.2014)
    Author:

      • IdentificationResponseMessage

        public IdentificationResponseMessage(java.lang.String loginName,
                                     java.lang.String playerName,
                                     java.lang.String password,
                                     java.lang.String reason,
                                     boolean loginSuccessful)
        Creates a new instance of IdentificationResponseMessage. This will set the user's name, the password, the failing reason (if there is any).
        Parameters:
        loginName - The user's login name
        playerName - The user's displayed name
        password - The user's password.
        reason - The reason why the log in failed (can be null)
        loginSuccessful - Flag that shows whether the login was successful or not
